'''Martin Township''' is one of ten [[Civil township|townships]] in [[Crawford County, Illinois|Crawford County]], [[Illinois]], [[United States|USA]].  As of the [[United States Census, 2000|2000 census]], its population was 607<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-context=dt&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_P001&-CONTEXT=dt&-tree_id=4001&-all_geo_types=N&-geo_id=06000US1703347202&-search_results=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en United States Census Bureau American FactFinder]</ref>.

==Geography==
According to the [[United States Census Bureau]], Martin Township covers an area of 42.58 square miles (110.29 square kilometers); of this, 0.01 square miles (0.03 square kilometers) or 0.03 percent is water.

===Unincorporated towns===
* [[Green Brier, Illinois|Green Brier]]
* [[Hardinville, Illinois|Hardinville]]
* [[Pierceburg, Illinois|Pierceburg]]
(This list is based on USGS data and may include former settlements.)

===Adjacent townships===
* [[Oblong Township, Crawford County, Illinois|Oblong Township]] (north)
* [[Robinson Township, Crawford County, Illinois|Robinson Township]] (northeast)
* [[Honey Creek Township, Crawford County, Illinois|Honey Creek Township]] (east)
* [[Southwest Township, Crawford County, Illinois|Southwest Township]] (south)
* [[Sainte Marie Township, Jasper County, Illinois|Sainte Marie Township, Jasper County]] (west)

===Cemeteries===
The township contains these five cemeteries: Berlin, Hardinville, Jones, Prior Grove and Richart.

==School districts==
* Oblong Community Unit School District 4
* Red Hill Community Unit School District 10
* Robinson Community Unit School District 2

==Political districts==
* [[Illinois' 15th congressional district]]
* State House District 109
* State Senate District 55

